==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anachronism
<hw>An*ach"ro*nism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'anachronismo`s</grk>, fr. <grk>'anachroni`zein</grk> to refer to a
wrong time, to confound times; <grk>'ana`</grk> + <grk>chro`nos</grk>
time: cf. F. <ets>anachronisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>A misplacing or error
in the order of time; an error in chronology by which events are
misplaced in regard to each other, esp. one by which an event is placed
too early; falsification of chronological relation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anachronistic</ent>⟦br⟧
